    "Yugoslav Hungarian Settlement By Council of League of Nations Amicable Adjustment Enables Europe to Weather Another Storm the Seriousness of Which Is Not Yet Clear Memories of 1914 Frances Suggestion for the Establishment by the League of a Permanent International Penal Court Weekly Be view of World Affaire a EUROPE weathered another storm during the week with the ami cable adjustment by the League Council of the quarrel between Yugoslavia and Hungary How bad a storm it was is not yet clear In Europe there was a good deal of alarm but this may have been due more to a vague feeling that in the Balkans anything can happen than to positive belief that war was near In our own country most people refused to get excited and they too probably had no reasoned belief in the matter but merely a general feeling that the powers would bellicose small coun tries from making trouble In the up shot this confidence was justified and the outcome was a credit to the states men and diplomats of Europe but the happy ending does not show that the danger was unreal Europe has sad reason in its belief that in the Bal kans"
